;
; sorcery_realtime_agents.conf.sample
;
; Tells Asterisk's PJSIP modules to look up their realtime objects via
; the unixODBC backend (mapped to Postgres in extconfig + res_odbc).
; Merge into /etc/asterisk/sorcery.conf.
;
; SECTION HEADERS MATTER. Asterisk's sorcery_realtime loader keys each
; type lookup on the section header, which must equal the name of the
; module that registered the sorcery type's config documentation via
; ast_sorcery_apply_config() — NOT just whichever .c file conceptually
; "owns" the type. Confirmed against this image's own
; /usr/share/asterisk/documentation/core-en_US.xml:
;
;   res_pjsip.c                          -> system, global, endpoint, auth,
;                                            aor, contact, domain_alias,
;                                            transport
;   res_pjsip_outbound_registration.c    -> registration
;   res_pjsip_endpoint_identifier_ip.c   -> identify
;
; `identify` looks like a core res_pjsip type (it's configured in
; pjsip.conf right alongside endpoint/aor/auth) but its <configInfo> block
; is registered by the separate res_pjsip_endpoint_identifier_ip module.
; Placing it under [res_pjsip] (as an earlier revision of this file did)
; makes sorcery_realtime log:
;   Cannot update type 'identify' in module 'res_pjsip' because it has
;   no existing documentation!
; ...which makes res_pjsip_endpoint_identifier_ip.so decline to load
; entirely (module show like identifier -> Not Running), so NO
; IP-based/carrier_ip trunk can ever be recognized on inbound, no
; matter how correct its ps_identify row is — carrier_ip-configured
; trunks silently reject all inbound with "No matching endpoint found".
;
; Likewise, if `registration` is placed under [res_pjsip] (as it was
; before an earlier revision), sorcery_realtime logs:
;   Cannot update type 'registration' in module 'res_pjsip'
; ...and silently drops the mapping, so res_pjsip_outbound_registration
; can't find its rows via realtime.
;

[res_pjsip]
endpoint=realtime,ps_endpoints
auth=realtime,ps_auths
aor=realtime,ps_aors

[res_pjsip_outbound_registration]
registration=realtime,ps_registrations

[res_pjsip_endpoint_identifier_ip]
identify=realtime,ps_identify
